            <entry xml:id="entry_cʼæj" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cʼæj</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cʼæjæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сукровица</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>serosanguinous fluid</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гной</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>gleet</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cæfæj ma cʼæj cæwy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из раны еще идет сукровица</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the serosanguinous fluid is still coming from the wound</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Относится к группе слов, выявляющих двоякие связи: с одной
                    стороны, с кавказскими, с другой — с угро-финскими языками (ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kært"/> ‘двор’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændon"/>
                    ‘сталь’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæxx"/> ‘соль’). На кавказской почве сюда
                    относятся: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼala</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼal</w>
                        <gloss><q>сукровица</q></gloss></mentioned> (%il%i — суффикс-детерминант,
                    корень %icʼa%i-), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>a-cʼa</w>
                        <gloss><q>гной</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼi</w>
                        <gloss><q>кровь</q></gloss></mentioned>. На угро-финской: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mns" dialect="mns"><lang/>
                        <w>säj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="smi"><lang/>
                        <w>säja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-mordvin"><lang/>
                        <w>sij</w>
                        <gloss><q>гной</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср.:
                            <bibl><author>Munkásсi</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Aria és
                            kaukàzusi eIemek а finn magyar nyeIvekben, стр.
                            241—242</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Aria és kaukàzusi eIemek а
                            finn magyar nyeIvekben, p. 241—242</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It relates to the group of words having double connections: one
                    the one hand, with Caucasian, on the other hand, with Finno-Ugric languages (cf.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kært"/> ‘yard’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ændon"/> ‘steel’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæxx"/>
                    ‘salt’). Cf. the following words in some Caucasian languages: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼala</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼal</w>
                        <gloss><q>serosanguinous fluid</q></gloss></mentioned> (%il%i is a
                    determinant suffix, the root is %icʼa%i-), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>a-cʼa</w>
                        <gloss><q>gleet</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼi</w>
                        <gloss><q>blood</q></gloss></mentioned>. Among Finno-Ugric langauges:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="mns" dialect="mns"><lang/>
                        <w>säj</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="smi"><lang/>
                        <w>säja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-mordvin"><lang/>
                        <w>sij</w>
                        <gloss><q>gleet</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf.:
                            <bibl><author>Munkáсsi.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Aria és
                            kaukàzusi eIemek а finn magyar nyeIvekben, стр.
                            241—242</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Aria és kaukàzusi eIemek а
                            finn magyar nyeIvekben, p. 241—242</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
            </entry>
